=====Explanation=====
We have provided 5 test cases to check the correctness of the solution function. The function takes a string input, where the first 3 numbers represent the coordinates of point A, the next 3 numbers represent the coordinates of point B, the next 3 numbers represent the coordinates of point C, and the last 3 numbers represent the coordinates of point D. The function should output the angle between the plane made by the points A, B, C and B, C, D in degrees(not radians).
